               Since I now will still remain a while in the mountains, I thank you from here for your great kindness in having returned so much of the consignment;

For notification of dispatch of this parcel, see J. Agardh to M, 23 August 1883 (in this edition as 83-08-23a).
                and I must fear that the advantages that you had from my consignments, after such an extensive return, are quite out of all proportion to your trouble! On all future occasions, if I may have the fortune to see your masterful experience turned to new consignments of algae, I ask you to retain whatever may be of interest for your own highly important collections. Of course I am pleased that your arduous sacrifice of time has procured a considerable number of surplus specimens for several other algologists, and I am also happy to see the Melbourne collection now also so very complete. With gratitude and respect your
